{"timestamp":"2026-05-06T19:05:01.101Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_fb5uwBN1eOkk1nULQpuWwif7","output":"Chunk ID: 08303a\nWall time: 0.7231 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 592\nOutput:\n{\"baseRefName\":\"main\",\"body\":\"1. **Stream-parse the pack** — wraps the upload reader with a `packfile.Scanner` running on an `io.Pipe`, exposing live `ObjectsSent()` / `TotalObjects()` atomics.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. **Abort early on projected overshoot** — uses those counters to cut a doomed upload at ~5% sent instead of waiting for the server to reject the full pack. `selfImposedBudget` ratchets down from observed cutoffs.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. **Use projection, not `sentBytes`, for factor & calibration** — fixes two bugs that fell out once the observer was wired up: subdivision factor was always 2 (because `sentBytes` after early abort was just the 8 MiB floor), and per-object calibration was diluted by dividing by the full pack count instead of objects actually observed.\\r\\n\\r\\nNet effect for blob-heavy repos: failed retries cost ~5% of pack size instead of 100%, and subdivision converges in 1–2 rounds instead of 6+.\\n\\n<!-- CURSOR_SUMMARY -->\\n---\\n\\n> [!NOTE]\\n> **Medium Risk**\\n> Adds concurrent streaming pack parsing and mid-upload abort logic in batched bootstrap pushes, which can change failure/retry behavior and introduce subtle concurrency/IO edge cases. Risk is mitigated by targeted unit tests for abort heuristics and observer behavior.\\n> \\n> **Overview**\\n> Batched bootstrap pushes now wrap pack uploads in a streaming `packStreamObserver` that counts bytes and parses the PACK stream via `packfile.Scanner` to track `ObjectsSent()`/`TotalObjects()`.\\n> \\n> On size-related failures (or self-triggered abort), the retry loop now **aborts doomed uploads early** using a projection-based `shouldAbortPush` heuristic and a ratcheting `selfImposedBudget`, and it **improves subdivision/calibration